Stolen from Keepers of Fortitude web site. By Thallus Carnivora  (so there)<br>
<br>
Well EFers , as you know it is (not) REQUIRED for you to have the ability to port to Thurgadin... the ONLY exception to this requirement is if you are a porting class. The reason we (don't) require this is for a few reasons: If we need to mobilize the guild fast, we can get everyone together no matter where they are... If you go LD in a bad spot and aren't able to get in far after the guild has left the area, this will save you and us from a hard CR. This is a quick and easy method to gain the ability to port.<br>
These were introduced into the game as a part of the 4th step of the Coldain Prayer Shawl Quest. <br>
<br>
Vial of Velium Vapors <br>
MAGIC ITEM LORE ITEM NO DROP <br>
EXPENDABLE CHARGES: 1 <br>
Effect: Thurgadin Gate <br>
WT: 1 SIZE: Small <br>
ALL/ALL <br>
<br>
First off, you need a pottery skill of around 120, where these are trivial ( See guide at bottom to get this skill up ) <br>
<br>
Go to Crystal Caverns and start farming! You need Crystilline Silk, Small Bricks of Velium, Small pieces of Velium. You will need these on a ratio of 3 : 1 : 2. <br>
<br>
The components you need for each potion are as follows: <br>
<br>
Velium Vial<br>
Combine on a pottery wheel: <br>
3 Crystilline Silks (from spiders in CC) <br>
1 Small Brick of Velium (from orc miners in CC) <br>
2 Glass Shards (from left-most vendor in Thurga bank) <br>
<br>
This results in an unfired vial. <br>
<br>
Combine in Kiln (oven right next to wheel): <br>
1 Unfired Vial <br>
1 High-quality Firing Sheet (from left most vendor in thurga bank) <br>
<br>
This results in a velium vial. <br>
<br>
Now, go out of the bank take a right and head towards the church (stay left at the fork). <br>
<br>
Inside the second merchie building on the left is Frundle Frenkler. Hail her and say &quot;What velium vapors?&quot; She tells you the recipe and gives you: <br>
<br>
Velium Purifier <br>
Container <br>
LORE ITEM NO DROP <br>
<br>
Combine in Velium Purifier <br>
1 Velium Vial <br>
2 Small Pieces of Velium <br>
<br>
The purifier will poof and you will be holding the Thurga gate potion... woot! <br>
<br>
The potion will gate you onto the bridge you cross when you enter Thurga.<br>
Easiest way to always have one in inventory is keep a few velium vials in the bank at all times and everytime you use one, grab your velium vial and 2 pieces of velium and go make another one.<br>
<br>
OK HOW TO GET YOUR POTTERY SKILL FROM 0 to 122 in ONE HOUR! <br>
<br>
0-102 Skill - <br>
Combine in pottery wheel: <br>
1 small block of clay <br>
1 bowl sketch <br>
1 water <br>
<br>
When this skill gets trivial at 102 switch to making Medium Bowls: <br>
<br>
103-122 <br>
1 medium bowl sketch <br>
1 block of clay <br>
1 water <br>
<br>
So there you have it! <br>
Note: (from randy)&lt;--- who is randy?   I have found that Thurgadin and Rivervale have all the materials and pottery wheel close together with least amount of running around.<br>
